
[1]broil

   BROIL,n. A tumult; a noisy quarrel; contention; discord,either between
   individuals or in the state.

   BROIL, v.t. To agitate with heat; to dress or cook over coals, before
   the fire; but more generally upon a gridiron over coals.

   BROIL, v.i. To be subjected to the action of heat, like meat over the
   fire; to be greatly heated or to sweat with heat.

   Where have you been broiling?
